item.title: CVE-2023-2029|2024-08-02T06:12:19.567Z -- unknown -- prepost%20seo
item.description: The PrePost SEO WordPress plugin through 3.0 does not properly sanitize some of its settings, which could allow high-privilege users to perform Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks even when the unfiltered_html capability is disallowed (for example in multisite setup)
